\begin_inset Formula $\overline{f'(a)}=\overline{\lim_{z\rightarrow a}\frac{f(z)-f(a)}{z-a}}=\lim_{\overline{z}\rightarrow\overline{a}}\frac{\overline{f(z)}-\overline{f(a)}}{\overline{z}-\overline{a}}$
\end_inset

